<br/></font> From the show:

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Runscope.com - testing van API’s</font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Teradici - beheerloos / OS-loos device voor AWS workspace (PCOIP zero clients)</font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Mainframe2 - ALL software in a browser</font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri">ScaleArc.com - Software Load balancing for databases (also Aurora) on Amazon</font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Ping Identity - Single Signon for the enterprise (pinging - single signon !!! )</font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	
	
	<div><span style="font-family: Times;"><br/></span></div>






	
	<hr/>Conflicting modification on 19 november 2014 09:41:34:
	
	<hr/>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Een aantal uitgangspunten</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- We (PNL) zullen in de komende 3 jaar moeten groeien naar een omvang van 30-35 FTE om (weer) een gezonde bedrijfsopbouw te hebben (verhouding overhead|productie). </div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Een tweede reden voor de noodzaak voor die groei ligt in het feit dat we nog met een aantal single point of failures zitten vwb de kennis die bij mensen aanwezig is.</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Uitgaande van een in de IT gebruikelijk omzet per FTE van zo’n 125K, hoort daar een omzet bij van tussen de 4MM en 4.5MM</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- meer dan 35 FTE mag, al wordt het pand dan te klein, maar wel met een verhouding van 125-150K / FTE.</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><font face="Calibri">- Minder dan 35FTE mag ook (bijvoorbeeld door te outsourcen naar andere Prisma vestigingen), dan moet de omzet/FTE dus stijgen.</font></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><font face="Calibri">- Prisma IT help onze klanten met het realiseren van online oplossingen. Daarvoor maken we gebruik van een “toolkit” of “lego blokken”. We zijn experts op het gebied van de verschillende tools (consultancy, training, licenties) en gebruiken die tools voor het realiseren van oplossingen.</font></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><font face="Calibri">- We zullen (zie ook het 2015 en beyond stuk) onszelf continu opnieuw moeten uitvinden. Dat uitvinden bestaat uit: nieuwe tools (platforms) vinden, expertise opbouwen (onze mensen trainen) en die nieuwe tools in onze toolkit opnemen. MBT de nieuwe tools kunnen we die expertise weer verkopen (consultancy, training, licenties), terwijl we de tools ook gebruiken in onze oplossingen. Dit is het continue vernieuwing proces (life-cycle) waarin we ons bevinden.</font></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Onze USP’s zitten in </div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">     a. expertise van de tools (Lego blokken) die we gebruiken en de interactie tussen die tools</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">     b. kennis van het ontwerpen en ontwikkelen van “user friendly” en “technisch en architectonisch hoogwaardige” online oplossingen. Vooral onze kennis van het koppelen van onze oplossingen aan “alles wat los en vast zit" (dus ook big-iron) wordt als waardevol gezien door externe experts</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Wat doen we? </div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Discover, Create, Deliver</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Development (ontwerp, architectuur, bouwen)</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Training, consulting &amp; mentoring</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Sysops (hosting)</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Licenties</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Wat gaan we (moeten we) toevoegen?</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Repeatable solutions (Alliant DXP, Alliant BI en Alliant BPM onder de verzamelnaam Alliant)</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Products (Morpheus)</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Mobile</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Wat gaan we veranderen?</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- (deels) uit de lineaire omzet proberen te komen. Dat kan alleen door een prijsopbouw mbv componenten (dus niet in een offerte “hosting XXX per jaar” opnemen, maar uitsplitsen).</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- een ingrijpende verandering wordt het embedden van de “Cloud architected” development methodieken, inclusief “continuous delivery” in onze ontwikkel methodieken. Dit zal een groot intern project zijn, maar het is mi absoluut noodzakelijk dit te gaan doen in 2015.</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Voor 2015 wil ik vasthouden aan een target van 2.6MM (afhankelijk van de omzet in 2014; we moeten 30% groeien in 2015). Als in het huidige sales plan “toegewerkt” wordt naar een target van 2.4MM, dan moet (met een aantal nieuwe en nog niet besproken zaken) 2.6 ZEKER haalbaar zijn.</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Onderverdeling:</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Complexe ontwikkel projecten, devops, continuous delivery</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Mobile</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- Piwik (iMetrix?)</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- licenties / trainingen / products</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- AWS consultancy, sysops &amp; trainingen</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">- repeatable solutions</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Dit zijn vwo sales bemanning (wellicht) geen full FTE’s (in het begin), maar kunnen m.i. zeker uitgroeien tot full FTE’s.</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">—> Ik zou (per direct) op zoek willen naar een dedicated sales rep voor licenties/trainingen/products (morpheus). Dit is een Fulltime functie, met een groot variabel salaris component</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">—> In Q1 moet er een sales rep voor Piwik/Mobile bijkomen (als we die combi kunnen vinden)</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">—> in Q1 moet er een sales rep voor AWS bijkomen</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">Bemensing development</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">hangt af van het aantal uren dat we gaan verkopen + goedgekeurde investeringen + hetgeen we gaan outsourcen naar andere vestigingen.</div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></div>

		
		<div style="font-family: Calibri;">

			
			<div>Gevoelsmatig moet er in Q1 een developer bij. In Q1 kunnen we kijken wat er in Q2 bij moet komen.</div>

		
		</div>

		
		<div><br/></div>

	
	</div>

	
	<div><br/></div>

	
	<div><br/></div>

	
	<div><br/></div>

	
	<div>

		
		<hr/>
	
	</div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Prisma IT Nederland BV - 2015 and beyond.</font></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">There is an old saying: “if you don’t rewrite your code, someone else will do it for you”. </font><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Every software company needs to continuously reinvent itself. In fact, it’s not only software companies that face this problem, car manufactures who would still produce horse carriages, would be out of business. The same is the fact for software companies, the only difference is that we tend to move faster than the rest of the world. An example: who had heard of “the Cloud” 3 years ago? And today, barely 3 years later, “the Cloud” is “the new normal”.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Prisma IT has always done this by scouting the market, finding an opportunity (programming language, platform or other), start to work with it, start delivering training, find customers who wanted software build with these tools and then adapt in the organization. This was the case with ColdFusion, Spectra, Flex, LiveCycle, Mura, frameworks, Webtrends etc.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">The reason why we have always succeeded is that there would always be one person, who would be the “evangelist” of the new language. For CF &amp; Flex that person was me, for LiveCycle it was Jochem, for frameworks Mark would often be an evangelist. Vincent for Webtrends, Ron for Brightcove and for Mura it is Guust.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">In the last few years we have not really been able to re-invent ourselves on a continuous basis. And that is starting to worry me more and more. We are falling behind and we run the risk of becoming “an average” IT provider. </font><font face="Calibri">I believe we have been in that danger zone for the last 2 or 3 years.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">The problem is, it is not due to that fact that we couldn’t find any new technologies, we have tried to adapt new technologies, but - apart from Mura and Brightcove - we havent really been able to do so. And having said that, I believe Mura and Brightcove aren’t the ones that will be able to “make the difference”. They are nice, but they will not be big differentiators.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Mendix, AWS training, BonitaSoft, DataLogics, DocOrigin are all technologies that we have not been able to adapt. And we let them slip.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">That needs  to change in 2 ways.</font></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">1. we need to start adapting new technologies</span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">2. we need to implement an ongoing process that enables point no. 1</span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">As a start, w</span><font face="Calibri">e need to have a discussion and build a plan around the idea to become a “Cloud Architected Software” centric company.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">What I have seen in November from AWS blew my mind. for the first time in over 14 years and for the 5th time in my career, I believe we found something that can help us push ourselves to the next stage. After DEC VAX, Apple Macintosh, ColdFusion and Flex, I believe Cloud centric (or cloud architected) *we need to find a better term* will completely change the paradigm of software development.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Over the last couple of years, AWS has been handled by us on the level of system management. We build applications, hand them over to sysmngmnt and they deploy. Either on our own hardware or in the cloud.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">We need to rapidly change this model. “Cloud awareness” needs to be handled at the architect level. We need to start designing and architecting our applications (projects, existing projects and repeatable solutions) around the possibilities that AWS provides.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">We also (and at the same time) need to change the way we develop. AWS tools like AWS CodeCommit, CodeDeploy CodePipeline, AWS Container Service, Docker and Apollo all need to be at the heart of our development methodologies.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Running the apps we build on AWS will be the new normal.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Technologies like AWS Lambda will fundamentally change the way we build software.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">At the same time we need to start projects and programs with sales and marketing to start talking to customers, add content on our website etc.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">We need to come up with a way to be able to adapt to new technologies and features that AWS releases. Just as an indication of the speed they are gaining: AWS has released more than 500 new technologies and features since Jan 1 2014.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">And the scary thing is that they build up even more speed with their releases.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">This will be a huge project for 2015 and it will mean that everybody needs to commit to this.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">We need to do this. It will be hard work and fun and it will make us better.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">I have created this text as the start of an internal discussion with management, team leads, sales &amp; marketing, developers and sysmngmnt on how to do this.</span><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">We can not afford to miss this one and we cannot afford to wait another year.</span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">Prisma IT needs to expand in 5 different focus areas in 2015</span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">- Revenues for PNL need to go up by 30% to 2.6MM</span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">- That would ratify a staff of between 20 and 26 FTE</span></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- The Alliant Solution Suite needs to be finalised and launched</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- We need to expand out international operations into different regions</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- We need to expand our solutions &amp; services offering with (at least) mobile &amp; Search optimalisation services (SEO, SEA etc)</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- We need to make AWS the core of our software Dev &amp; Ops work. AWS needs to be included at the architectural level of what we do</font></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">We have already started to refocus from “selling hours” to “selling a solution”. Currently pricing of solutions is still based on the work needed for the solution. We need to continue changing this and introducing license models.</font></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">We need to continue to get out of the “linear” revenue model (which is what selling hours is)</font></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;">Just based on workforce, our financial capacity is 200 days * 8 hours * 9 employees * € 85,- = 1.2MM</span></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">This number is high. People are not 100% billable and our many of our people are not full FTE’s.</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">Further, we must complete a number of internal projects:</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Single Signon for all Prisma IT services (Through PingONe?)</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Phase out of international servers</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Move Domain controllers to the cloud</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Move all backups to the cloud</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Move Fileshares to the cloud (Sharepoint, Zocalo or other?)</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Move dev environments (of non-standard environments) to EC2?</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Update &amp; Professionalize WIFI at HQ</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Setup a Prisma IT blog</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- Make sure new clients/projects/releases are on our website on the day of the release</font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri">- </font></div>

	
	<div><font face="Calibri"><br/></font></div>

	
	<div><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><br/></span></div>

	
	<div>

		
		<hr/>
	
	</div>

	
	<div><br/></div>

	
	<div><span style="mso-ansi-language:EN-US">PINT version 2015</span></div>

	
	<div>

		
		<div><i style="mso-bidi-font-style:normal"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN-US">“Prisma IT is dedicated to helping you realize superior digital solutions”. Founded in 1992 and headquartered in Rotterdam, we are a Pan-European organization with offices in multiple countries. Our down-to-earth approach and proven commitment to providing our clients the right solutions, the best technology available worldwide and qualified professionals, have made us the partner of choice for public and private organizations of all sizes around the world. Our consultants, trainers and engineers are industry experts in rich media and cloud technologies. We leverage these technologies, our craftsmanship and our experience to help our clients realize business critical applications as well as rich online content delivery solutions across devices. You can find us at <a href="http://prisma-it.com">prisma-it.com</a>.</span></i></div>

		
		<div><i style="mso-bidi-font-style:normal"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size:9.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN-US"> </span></i></div>

		
